Very good. The biggest issue with finding a good Harold's is locating one that actually has the traditional Harold's flavoring and/or taste. The location absolutely stays true to that flavor you look for when visiting a Harold's Chicken restaurant. The service is good and the wait for you food is pretty quick as far as made to order food goes. You won't be disappointed here.

The Good: Food is very good as long as you're specific, and it's plentiful!  The bad: Can't call in your food orders over the phone unless you pay with a card and give them your card number+cvv over the phone.  The Very Bad: If you order in the restaurant be prepared for an average wait of 20+ minutes, so unless you have a lengthy lunch break... skip this place.
Rarely answer the phone.

I called at around 130p on Tue, 15 Dec and the young lady that answered the phone was polite, prompt, and effective. I forgot to ask for the mild sauce and was devastated but she took my request and was a gem about it. She deserves a shout out and a raise. Not many places have people like that working the phones.

Unsatisfied to the service and the food I got. First the cashier doesn’t know their menu. I asked about the giblets on menu she said she doesn’t knew. Then she was talking on the phone all through out the time I received my order without wearing face mask. Despite it is posted on their wall to wear face mask. Second I was cheated on the gizzard that I ordered. It was only few pieces and at the bottom of it are lots of fries and underneath was a slice of bread to make it looks full. I don’t mind the 17 percent charges for COVID-19. But to cheat on your customer is a no no... so disappointed!!!

Harold’s is amazing! So happy to have them in my neighborhood. The food is so fresh, super generous portions, and that sauce! Just the right amount of heat. The breading is crispy and savory. Deep fried to perfection. And don’t forget the slaw. The staff is always super friendly and how about the chef?! He works some chicken magic back there! Do yourself a favor and get some!!

For a Harold's chicken not on the south side this harold's is actually very well done. Prepared enough fries, asks if you want the coleslaw (sometimes they just provide the coleslaw regardless), mild and hot sauce very clean. This place definitely uses clean grease, good chicken and very fresh bread to guard the sauces and grease from going through the bucket that the food comes in. Would highly recommend this to anyone on the north side (or if you're not from the north side and are in the area). Only downside is parking but it is a small thing to overlook for great food.

I have ordered from this Harolds 3 times in the past two months and specifically ordered the catfish dinner and received perch instead of catfish all three times. After calling the restaurant to speak to a manager I was told that “they don’t have one” by a female employee and was then put on the phone with the “chef”. After she walked away from the phone to complain about me calling, which I could still hear over the phone, the so called “chef” was argumentative and unable to understand the difference between the two very different types of fish that they serve. I would highly recommend that if you like Harold’s Chicken that you go else where because this location has been a horrible experience.

This is one of the friendliest places I have been to in Chicago. The staff is great! Had small conversation with the guy that took our order while we waited for our food. This was our first time coming in. We were able to take our time, ask questions and get help on what to pick for lunch. Even as we left the guy that helped us chased us down to give us our coleslaw. That's some awesome service right there. I tried the chicken sandwich which is amazing and a small thing of fried livers which were also amazing. Food is made to order but we waited no more than 10 minutes. They do have safety precautions in place. I highly recommend this place not only for the good food but for the friendly service, which makes all the difference in going to a restaurant.

So happy to have a harolds chicken on the northside. The young man at the counter was so pleasant and upbeat. Wasnt a crazy long wait for food as all HC are made to order. And good desserts now too not just butter cookies like the franchises in the old days😀 Welcome to the northside!

This review has nothing to do with the staff or the quality of the food but with how the owner treated a customer service issue. My partner and I ordered food from here for pick-up, which one of the staff members gave to someone else by mistake (either a grub hub driver or another patron). When the staff member called the owner to ask what should be done, the owner basically said, do nothing because they can't give out food since another truck won't be coming for a while. I am truly appalled at the lack of customer service. The restaurant would not give us our food or money back due to a mistake that they made under the advice of the owner.
